<sec id="sec011" class="sec">
 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Gains in constructs</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The EFA identifies a number of constructs capturing participants’ knowledge of climate change, their affective engagement with the issue, and their intent to take action to address the problem. Here we assess whether World Climate led to changes in these constructs.</p>
 <sec id="sec012" sec-type="materials|methods" class="sec">
  <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Methods</div>
  <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Two-tailed paired t-tests were used to test for statistically significant shifts in the values of constructs or selected items from the pre- to post-surveys. The magnitude of differences between the post- and pre-survey means is assessed by Cohen’s 
   <span class="italic">d</span> [
